Update: Made the remaining requested change from the previous review, then merged with the latest changes from main. On merging, I found that python_op_gen_main.cc now uses the routines in python_eager_op_gen.cc instead of using python_op_gen.cc. So I moved the code that adds the "Original C++ source" notice over to python_eager_op_gen.cc. I ran the build, verified that the generated files still get "original c++ source" notices, and ran all the unit tests under //tensorflow/python/....

On a side note, the code in python_op_gen.cc and python_op_gen.h doesn't appear to be called from anywhere any more. Is that intentional?

body:
Update: Made the remaining requested change from the previous review, then merged with the latest changes from main. On merging, I found that `python_op_gen_main.cc` now uses the routines in `python_eager_op_gen.cc` instead of using `python_op_gen.cc`. So I moved the code that adds the "Original C++ source" notice over to `python_eager_op_gen.cc`. I ran the build, verified that the generated files still get "original c++ source" notices, and ran all the unit tests under `//tensorflow/python/...`.

On a side note, the code in `python_op_gen.cc` and `python_op_gen.h` doesn't appear to be called from anywhere any more. Is that intentional?
